        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 7:05PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 705 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Tuppers Plains, or 8 miles north of Pomeroy, moving
southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pomeroy, Racine, Forked Run State Park, New Haven, Mason, Tuppers
Plains, Middleport, Chester, Syracuse, Hartford City, Belleville,
Reedsville, Darwin, and Harrisonville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
